My comment on Hitler was motivated my Charles' comment that<br>
&quot;only about 10,000,000 such crimes can be attributed to Hitler&quot;. My point is that all of this stuff is bad, whether it be communist or nazi. As to who was worse, it does not matter. At what point do we stop counting and condemn the whole lot? Perhaps the word &quot;only&quot; was that which triggered me on this! Hitler's body count per *year* probably equalled that of Stalin. Tyranical bloodthristy dictators are all the same, no matter what name they go by or reasons they use for their actions. <br><br>
